# Cursor Rules for Unity Project

## Code Style
- Use C# naming conventions
- Prefer async/await over callbacks
- Use Unity's Debug.Log for logging
- Follow SOLID principles

## Unity Specific
- Always use SerializeField for inspector fields
- Prefer ScriptableObjects for configuration
- Use Unity's Job System for heavy computations
- Optimize for mobile performance

## Performance
- Cache frequently accessed components
- Use object pooling for frequently instantiated objects
- Avoid allocations in Update/FixedUpdate
- Profile regularly with Unity Profiler